com.ucsf.core.data

Class DataManager.Table

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ucsf.core.data.DataManager.Table
  • Enclosing class:
    DataManager

    public class DataManager.Table
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing a database table. Tables are uniquely identified by a name and a device location.

      • fetch

        public DataManager.Cursor fetch(java.lang.String[] entriesTags,
                                java.lang.String[] modifiers,
                                DataManager.Condition... conditions)
                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Fetch all modified entries of the given types matching the given conditions. For instance, the modifier "count" will return the number of entries matching the given conditions. The database must have been opened before (see DataManager.get(Context)).
        Parameters:
        entriesTags - List of the field tags to fetch.
        modifiers - Modifiers to apply to the given field tags. If a modifier is null or and empty string, just fetch the corresponding field.
        conditions - List of conditions to satisfy. See DataManager.Condition for supported conditions.
        Returns:
        Returns null if an error occurs or a cursor pointing to the requested entries.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • fetch

        public DataManager.Cursor fetch(int limit,
                                java.lang.String[] entriesTags,
                                java.lang.String[] modifiers,
                                DataManager.Condition... conditions)
                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Fetch all modified entries of the given types matching the given conditions up to the given limit. For instance, the modifier "count" will return the number of entries matching the given conditions. The database must have been opened before (see DataManager.get(Context)).
        Parameters:
        limit - Maximal number of entries to fetch.
        entriesTags - List of the field tags to fetch.
        modifiers - Modifiers to apply to the given field tags. If a modifier is null or and empty string, just fetch the corresponding field.
        conditions - List of conditions to satisfy. See DataManager.Condition for supported conditions.
        Returns:
        Returns null if an error occurs or a cursor pointing to the requested entries.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • fetchAndAdd

        public boolean fetchAndAdd(Entry[] conditions,
                           Entry... entries)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Fetch if the given entries exists. If true, update them. Otherwise add new entries. The database must have been opened before (see DataManager.get(Context)).
        Parameters:
        entries - List of entries to update. An entry is composed of the field tag and the value to insert.
        conditions - List of entries to fetch. If no match found, those entries will be inserted together with the other entries.
        Returns:
        Returns if the operation is successful.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
